THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF NEVADA, REPRESENTED IN
SENATE AND ASSEMBLY, DO ENACT AS FOLLOWS:
1 Section 1. Chapter 427A of NRS is hereby amended by adding thereto a new
2 section to read as follows:
3 1. The Division shall establish and administer a program for dementia care
4 specialists in this State.
5 2. The program established pursuant to this section must have as its goals,
6 without limitation:
7 (a) To develop and provide crisis intervention services for persons with
8 dementia and their families and caregivers, including, without limitation, services
9 that provide an initial crisis response, crisis stabilization and long-term care for
10 persons with dementia who exhibit behavioral problems.
11 (b) To proactively support persons with dementia and their families and
12 caregivers to ensure the highest quality of life possible and to enable persons with
13 dementia to remain in their own homes or with family and avoid placement in a
14 facility for long-term care by, without limitation:
15 (1) Providing information, assistance, education and support to persons
16 with dementia and their families and caregivers;
17 (2) Facilitating the development of communities in this State where
18 persons with dementia may remain safe and active;
19 (3) Providing training to governmental agencies and nonprofit
20 organizations that provide services to persons with dementia; and
21 (4) Raising awareness of and developing community support for persons
22 with dementia and their families and caregivers.
23 (c) To assist persons with dementia and their families and caregivers with
24 limited English proficiency by providing access to the program through, without
25 limitation, translation and interpretation services.
26 3. Within the limits of legislative appropriations and any other money
27 available for this purpose, the Division shall:
28 (a) Prepare requests for proposals for the provision of services by dementia
29 care specialists employed by local governmental agencies or nonprofit
30 organizations to carry out the program established pursuant to this section. The
31 Division shall establish such requirements for the requests for proposals as it
32 determines necessary.
33 (b) Partner or contract with an appropriate educational organization to:
34 (1) Provide training to dementia care specialists.
35 (2) Evaluate the program established pursuant to this section.

