8 Sec. 2. Chapter 439 of NRS is hereby amended by adding thereto a new
9 section to read as follows:
10 1. The University of Nevada, Las Vegas, School of Medicine and the
11 University of Nevada, Reno, School of Medicine, in collaboration with the
12 Department, may establish the Nevada Memory Network in accordance with this
13 section. If the Nevada Memory Network is established, the University of Nevada,
14 Las Vegas, School of Medicine, the University of Nevada, Reno, School of
15 Medicine and the Department shall:
16 (a) Establish or contract with clinics that employ or contract with physicians
17 who specialize in neurology, neuropsychology and geriatrics to:
18 (1) Train providers of primary care in screening for and treating
19 dementia;
20 (2) Diagnose dementia in patients referred to the clinics by providers of
21 primary care;
22 (3) Create plans of care for patients with dementia; and
23 (4) Use telehealth where necessary or convenient to carry out the duties
24 prescribed in subparagraphs (1), (2) and (3).
25 (b) Employ or contract with community health workers who specialize in
26 dementia care. The community health workers shall:
27 (1) Coordinate care and provide referrals to community-based services
28 and in-home care for patients diagnosed with dementia pursuant to
29 subparagraph (2) of paragraph (a); and
30 (2) Monitor the well-being of and provide support to persons who provide
31 care to patients diagnosed with dementia pursuant to subparagraph (2) of
32 paragraph (a), including, without limitation, providers of respite care to such
33 patients.
34 (c) Contract with community-based organizations to:
35 (1) Develop and provide crisis intervention services for persons
36 diagnosed with dementia and their families and caregivers, including, without
37 limitation, providing initial crisis response and crisis stabilization services;
38 (2) Provide long-term care for persons diagnosed with dementia who
39 exhibit behavioral problems; and
40 (3) Proactively support persons diagnosed with dementia and their
41 families and caregivers to ensure the highest quality of life possible and to enable
42 persons diagnosed with dementia to remain in their own homes or with family
43 and avoid placement in a facility for long-term care by, without limitation:
44 (I) Providing information, assistance, education and support to
45 persons diagnosed with dementia and their families and caregivers;
46 (II) Facilitating the development of communities in this State where
47 persons diagnosed with dementia may remain safe and active;
48 (III) Providing training to governmental agencies and nonprofit
49 organizations that provide services to persons diagnosed with dementia; and
50 (IV) Raising awareness of and developing community support for
51 persons diagnosed with dementia and their families and caregivers.
52 2. The University of Nevada, Las Vegas, School of Medicine, the University
53 of Nevada, Reno, School of Medicine and the Department may collaborate or

